==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Manyplies
<hw>Ma"ny*plies</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Many</ets>,
adj. + <ets>plies</ets>, pl. of <ets>ply</ets> a fold.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The third division, or that between the
reticulum, or honeycomb stomach, and the abomasum, or rennet stomach, in
the stomach of ruminants; the omasum; the psalterium. So called from the
numerous folds in its mucous membrane. See <xex>Illust</xex> of
<er>Ruminant</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Many-sided</ent>⟦br⟧
